Name: 303 Hampton Rd, South Fremantle
Description: North of Rockingham Road, Hampton Road should be a 50 zone (or less). Very difficult for pedestrians to cross at any point. VERY short pedestrian-cross phase at lights. Very dangerous turning right on or off Hampton Road as few breaks in traffic causes risk taking. Very high traffic zone in a long-standing problem area with various unsuccessful 'fixes' over the years. Bus lane often used by  frustrated regular traffic = dangerous for pedestrians & cyclists. Too many close traffic lights. SLOW IT

Best opportunity is when the traffic light is red and cars will stop to let you in, but there is a green light for traffic turning left, so it is dangerous and hard to judge when it's safe to cross.
